evision. The mix of arts and cultural studies methodologies makes for an unusual and insightful approach.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aTelevision programszGreat Britain. 0aTelevision programszUnited States. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2021. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Television / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aTV drama.  aaesthetics of texts.  acultural trends.  aeconomics.  aglobal market-place.  ainstitutions.  aquality.  atelevision.  avalue shift.  aviewer preference.1 aNelson, Robin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779182540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847791825423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847791825/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles